 <setSpec>math</setSpec>
</header>
<metadata>
 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.3652</id><submitter>Tewodros Amdeberhan</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Fri, 21 Nov 2008 23:31:49 GMT</date><size>32kb</size></version><title>Polynomial Coefficient Enumeration</title><authors>Tewodros Amdeberhan and Richard P. Stanley</authors><categories>math.CO math.NT</categories><comments>36 pages</comments><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  Let $f(x_1,...,x_k)$ be a polynomial over a field $K$. This paper considers
such questions as the enumeration of the number of nonzero coefficients of $f$
or of the number of coefficients equal to $\alpha\in K^*$. For instance, if
$K=\ff_q$ then a matrix formula is obtained for the number of coefficients of
$f^n$ that are equal to $\alpha\in \ff_q^*$, as a function of $n$. Many
additional results are obtained related to such areas as lattice path
enumeration and the enumeration of integer points in convex polytopes.
</abstract></arXivRaw>
