 <id>0811.3656</id><submitter>Gerardo Ortiz</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Sat, 22 Nov 2008 02:49:46 GMT</date><size>12kb</size></version><title>Ferrotoroidic Moment as a Quantum Geometric Phase</title><authors>C. D. Batista, G. Ortiz, and A. A. Aligia</authors><categories>cond-mat.str-el</categories><journal-ref>Physical Review Letters 101, 077203 (2008)</journal-ref><doi>10.1103/PhysRevLett.101.077203</doi><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  We present a geometric characterization of the ferrotoroidic moment in terms
of a set of Abelian Berry phases. We also introduce a fundamental complex
quantity which provides an alternative way to calculate the ferrotoroidic
moment and its moments, and is derived from a second order tensor. This
geometric framework defines a natural computational approach for density
functional and many-body theories.
</abstract></arXivRaw>
