<metadata>
 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.3680</id><submitter>Quirino Sugon Jr.</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Mon, 24 Nov 2008 04:38:07 GMT</date><size>17kb</size></version><title>A geometric algebra reformulation of 2x2 matrices: the dihedral group
  D_4 in bra-ket notation</title><authors>Quirino M. Sugon Jr., Carlo B. Fernandez, and Daniel J. McNamara</authors><categories>math-ph math.MP</categories><comments>11 pages, 3 figures, 1 table</comments><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  We represent vector rotation operators in terms of bras or kets of half-angle
exponentials in Clifford (geometric) algebra Cl_{3,0}. We show that SO_3 is a
rotation group and we define the dihedral group D_4 as its finite subgroup. We
use the Euler-Rodrigues formulas to compute the multiplication table of D_4 and
derive its group algebra identities. We take the linear combination of rotation
operators in D_4 to represent the four Fermion matrices in Sakurai, which in
turn we use to decompose any 2x2 matrix. We show that bra and ket operators
generate left- and right-acting matrices, respectively. We also show that the
Pauli spin matrices are not vectors but vector rotation operators, except for
\sigma_2 which requires a subsequent multiplication by the imaginary number i
geometrically interpreted as the unit oriented volume.
</abstract></arXivRaw>
