<metadata>
 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.3733</id><submitter>Nadir Matringe</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Sun, 23 Nov 2008 17:27:46 GMT</date><size>11kb</size></version><version version='v10'><date>Thu, 10 Sep 2009 12:08:11 GMT</date><size>21kb</size></version><version version='v11'><date>Wed, 21 Oct 2009 15:10:15 GMT</date><size>28kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Wed, 26 Nov 2008 07:46:01 GMT</date><size>11kb</size></version><version version='v3'><date>Sat, 13 Dec 2008 20:57:04 GMT</date><size>13kb</size></version><version version='v4'><date>Sat, 28 Feb 2009 19:00:57 GMT</date><size>13kb</size></version><version version='v5'><date>Fri, 13 Mar 2009 19:48:31 GMT</date><size>19kb</size></version><version version='v6'><date>Mon, 16 Mar 2009 05:28:00 GMT</date><size>20kb</size></version><version version='v7'><date>Tue, 17 Mar 2009 14:40:20 GMT</date><size>20kb</size></version><version version='v8'><date>Sat, 4 Apr 2009 11:26:07 GMT</date><size>20kb</size></version><version version='v9'><date>Wed, 24 Jun 2009 12:24:56 GMT</date><size>21kb</size></version><title>Distinction of some induced representations</title><authors>Nadir Matringe (IMJ)</authors><categories>math.RT</categories><comments>An important mistake in the previous version has been corrected here</comments><proxy>ccsd hal-00340843</proxy><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  Let $K/F$ be a quadratic extension of $p$-adic fields, $\sigma$ the
nontrivial element of the Galois group of $K$ over $F$, and $\pi$ a
quasi-square-integrable representation of $GL(n,K)$. Denoting by $\pi^{\vee}$
the smooth contragredient of $\pi$, and by $\pi^{\sigma}$ the representation
$\pi\circ \sigma$, we show that the representation of $GL(2n, K)$ obtained by
normalized parabolic induction of the representation $\pi^\vee \otimes
\pi^\sigma$ is distinguished with respect to $GL(2n,F)$. This is a step towards
the classification of distinguished generic representations of general linear
groups over $p$-adic fields.
