 <id>0811.3792</id><submitter>Liang Xiao</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Mon, 24 Nov 2008 02:44:25 GMT</date><size>46kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Sun, 24 Jul 2011 19:00:15 GMT</date><size>55kb</size></version><title>On Ramification Filtrations and p-adic Differential Equations, II: mixed
  characteristic case</title><authors>Liang Xiao</authors><categories>math.NT</categories><msc-class>11S15</msc-class><doi>10.1112/S0010437X1100707X</doi><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  Let K be a complete discretely valued field of mixed characteristic (0, p)
with possibly imperfect residue field. We prove a Hasse-Arf theorem for the
arithmetic ramification filtrations on G_K, except possibly in the absolutely
unramified and non-logarithmic case, or p=2 and logarithmic case. As an
application, we obtain a Hasse-Arf theorem for filtrations on finite flat group
schemes over O_K.
