<metadata>
 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.3830</id><submitter>Anargyros Katsabekis</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Mon, 24 Nov 2008 09:58:29 GMT</date><size>13kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Fri, 8 May 2009 14:06:00 GMT</date><size>14kb</size></version><title>Specializations of multigradings and the arithmetical rank of lattice
  ideals</title><authors>Anargyros Katsabekis, Apostolos Thoma</authors><categories>math.AC math.AG</categories><comments>14 pages</comments><msc-class>14M25;13F55</msc-class><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  In this article we study specializations of multigradings and apply them to
the problem of the computation of the arithmetical rank of a lattice ideal
$I_{L_{\mathcal{G}}} \subset K[x_{1},...,x_{n}]$. The arithmetical rank of
$I_{L_{\mathcal{G}}}$ equals the $\mathcal{F}$-homogeneous arithmetical rank of
$I_{L_{\mathcal{G}}}$, for an appropriate specialization $\mathcal{F}$ of
$\mathcal{G}$. To the lattice ideal $I_{L_{\mathcal{G}}}$ and every
specialization $\mathcal{F}$ of $\mathcal{G}$ we associate a simplicial
complex. We prove that combinatorial invariants of the simplicial complex
provide lower bounds for the $\mathcal{F}$-homogeneous arithmetical rank of
$I_{L_{\mathcal{G}}}$.
