 <id>0811.3836</id><submitter>Vladimir Tretyak</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Mon, 24 Nov 2008 10:35:03 GMT</date><size>9kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Thu, 7 May 2009 01:16:10 GMT</date><size>9kb</size></version><title>Heat flow of the Earth and resonant capture of solar 57-Fe axions</title><authors>F.A. Danevich, A.V. Ivanov, V.V. Kobychev, V.I. Tretyak</authors><categories>nucl-ex</categories><comments>8 pages</comments><journal-ref>Kinematics and Physics of Celestial Bodies 25 (2009) 102-106</journal-ref><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  In a very conservative approach, supposing that total heat flow of the Earth
is exclusively due to resonant capture inside the Earth of axions, emitted by
57-Fe nuclei on Sun, we obtain limit on mass of hadronic axion: m_a&lt;1.8 keV.
Taking into account release of heat from decays of 40-K, 232-Th, 238-U inside
the Earth, this estimation could be improved to the value: m_a&lt;1.6 keV. Both
the values are less restrictive than limits set in devoted experiments to
search for 57-Fe axions (m_a&lt;216-745 eV), but are much better than limits
obtained in experiments with 83-Kr (m_a&lt;5.5 keV) and 7-Li (m_a&lt;13.9-32 keV).
