<metadata>
 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.3841</id><submitter>Peter B. Gilkey</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Mon, 24 Nov 2008 11:20:39 GMT</date><size>9kb</size></version><title>Riemannian geometric realizations for Ricci tensors of generalized
  algebraic curvature operators</title><authors>P. Gilkey, S. Nikcevic, D. Westerman</authors><categories>math.DG</categories><msc-class>53B20</msc-class><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  We examine questions of geometric realizability for algebraic structures
which arise naturally in affine and Riemannian geometry. Suppose given an
algebraic curvature operator R at a point P of a manifold M and suppose given a
real analytic (resp. C-k for finite k at least 2) pseudo-Riemannian metric on M
defined near P. We construct a torsion free real analytic (resp. C-k)
connection D which is defined near P on the tangent bundle of M whose curvature
operator is the given operator R at P and so that D has constant scalar
curvature. We show that if R is Ricci symmetric, then D can be chosen to be
Ricci symmetric; if R has trace free Ricci tensor, then D can be chosen to have
trace free Ricci tensor; if R is Ricci alternating, then D can be chosen to be
Ricci alternating.
</abstract></arXivRaw>
