 <id>0811.3843</id><submitter>Alejandro Bermudez</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Mon, 24 Nov 2008 11:22:36 GMT</date><size>313kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Mon, 9 Mar 2009 09:45:51 GMT</date><size>65kb</size></version><title>Topology induced anomalous defect production by crossing a quantum
  critical point</title><authors>A. Bermudez, D. Patan\`e, L. Amico, and M. A. Martin-Delgado</authors><categories>cond-mat.str-el hep-th quant-ph</categories><comments>Phys. Rev. Lett. (to be published)</comments><journal-ref>Phys. Rev. Lett. 102, 135702 (2009)</journal-ref><doi>10.1103/PhysRevLett.102.135702</doi><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  We study the influence of topology on the quench dynamics of a system driven
