mappings with a collectionwise normal domain can be reduced only to
compact-valued mappings modulo Dowker's extension theorem for such spaces. The
idea used to achieve this reduction is also applied to get a simple direct
proof of that selection theorem of Michael's. Some other possible applications
are demonstrated as well.
