<metadata>
 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.4001</id><submitter>Eduardo Martinez-Pedroza</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Tue, 25 Nov 2008 00:19:37 GMT</date><size>22kb</size><source_type>D</source_type></version><version version='v2'><date>Thu, 23 Jul 2009 14:54:33 GMT</date><size>31kb</size><source_type>D</source_type></version><version version='v3'><date>Wed, 12 May 2010 22:35:40 GMT</date><size>31kb</size><source_type>D</source_type></version><title>Separation of Relatively Quasiconvex Subgroups</title><authors>Jason Fox Manning, Eduardo Martinez-Pedroza</authors><categories>math.GR math.GT</categories><comments>22 pages, 2 figures. New version has numbering matching with the
  published version in the Pacific Journal of Mathematics, 244 no. 2 (2010)
  309--334.</comments><msc-class>20F65, 20F67, 20E26</msc-class><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  Suppose that all hyperbolic groups are residually finite. The following
statements follow: In relatively hyperbolic groups with peripheral structures
consisting of finitely generated nilpotent subgroups, quasiconvex subgroups are
separable; Geometrically finite subgroups of non-uniform lattices in rank one
symmetric spaces are separable; Kleinian groups are subgroup separable. We also
show that LERF for finite volume hyperbolic 3-manifolds would follow from LERF
for closed hyperbolic 3-manifolds.
  The method is to reduce, via combination and filling theorems, the
separability of a quasiconvex subgroup of a relatively hyperbolic group G to
the separability of a quasiconvex subgroup of a hyperbolic quotient G/N. A
result of Agol, Groves, and Manning is then applied.
</abstract></arXivRaw>
