 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.4010</id><submitter>Dong Sheng</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Tue, 25 Nov 2008 03:37:56 GMT</date><size>258kb</size></version><title>Lifetime measurements of the 5d states of rubidium</title><authors>D. Sheng and A. Perez Galvan and L. A. Orozco</authors><categories>physics.atom-ph</categories><comments>9 pages, 6 figures</comments><doi>10.1103/PhysRevA.78.062506</doi><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  We present lifetime measurements of the $5D_{3/2}$ and $5D_{5/2}$ states of
rubidium using the time correlated single photon counting method. We perform
the experiment in a magneto-optical trap of $^{87}$Rb atoms using a two-step
excitation with the trap laser at 780 nm as the first step. We record the 761.9
nm fluorescence from the decay of the $5D_{3/2}$ state to the $5P_{1/2}$ state,
and measure the lifetime of the $5D_{3/2}$ state $\tau=246.3(1.6)$ ns. We
record the 420.2 nm fluorescence from the cascade decay of the $5D_{5/2}$ state
to the $5S_{1/2}$ state through the $6P_{3/2}$ state, and extract the lifetime
of the $5D_{5/2}$ state ${\tau}=238.5(2.3)$ ns.
