 <id>0811.4079</id><submitter>Rodolphe Garbit</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Tue, 25 Nov 2008 13:07:37 GMT</date><size>23kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Fri, 28 Nov 2008 13:28:29 GMT</date><size>24kb</size></version><version version='v3'><date>Sat, 6 Jun 2009 19:23:50 GMT</date><size>16kb</size></version><title>Brownian motion conditioned to stay in a cone</title><authors>Rodolphe Garbit (LMJL)</authors><categories>math.PR</categories><proxy>ccsd hal-00341032</proxy><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  A result of R. Durrett, D. Iglehart and D. Miller states that Brownian
meander is Brownian motion conditioned to stay positive for a unit of time, in
the sense that it is the weak limit, as $x$ goes to 0, of Brownian motion
started at $x&gt;0$ and conditioned to stay positive for a unit of time. We extend
this limit theorem to the case of multidimensional Brownian motion conditioned
to stay in a smooth convex cone.
