 <id>0811.4093</id><submitter>Yang Sun</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Tue, 25 Nov 2008 14:23:29 GMT</date><size>54kb</size></version><title>Shell gaps and pn pairing interaction in N = Z nuclei</title><authors>Kazunari Kaneko, Jing-ye Zhang, Yang Sun</authors><categories>nucl-th nucl-ex</categories><comments>9 pages, 5 figures</comments><journal-ref>Phys.Lett.B671:42-45,2009</journal-ref><doi>10.1016/j.physletb.2008.11.072</doi><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  We analyze the observed shell gaps in N=Z nuclei determined from the binding
energy differences. It is found that the shell gaps can be described by the
combined contributions from the single-particle level spacing, the like-nucleon
