Kyoto workshop on Resolution of Singularities in Positive Characteristic,
December 2008.
  The article surveys the theory of kangaroo points as they appear in the
resolution of singularities in positive characteristic. They represent one of
the main obstructions for transcribing the characteristic zero proof of
resolution to positive characteristic. Kangaroo points are classified through
the concept of oblique polynomials. The results of the article are used in
Hironaka's recent program towards the resolution of singularities in positive
characteristic.
