 <id>0811.4269</id><submitter>Khedmat Atazadeh</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Wed, 26 Nov 2008 10:53:50 GMT</date><size>12kb</size></version><title>Energy conditions in f(R) gravity and Brans-Dicke theories</title><authors>K. Atazadeh, A. Khaleghi, H. R. Sepangi, Y. Tavakoli</authors><categories>gr-qc hep-th</categories><comments>9 pages, 1 figure, to appear in IJMPD</comments><journal-ref>Int.J.Mod.Phys.D18:1101-1111,2009</journal-ref><doi>10.1142/S0218271809014972</doi><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  The equivalence between f(R) gravity and scalar-tensor theories is invoked to
study the null, strong, weak and dominant energy conditions in Brans-Dicke
theory. We consider the validity of the energy conditions in Brans-Dicke theory
by invoking the energy conditions derived from a generic f(R) theory. The
parameters involved are shown to be consistent with an accelerated expanding
universe.
