 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.4284</id><submitter>Katharine Challis</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Wed, 26 Nov 2008 12:31:07 GMT</date><size>111kb</size><source_type>D</source_type></version><title>Scattering Resonances in a Degenerate Fermi Gas</title><authors>K. J. Challis, N. Nygaard, K. M{\o}lmer</authors><categories>cond-mat.other</categories><comments>8 pages, 5 figures</comments><journal-ref>Phys. Rev. A 79, 052701 (2009)</journal-ref><doi>10.1103/PhysRevA.79.052701</doi><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  We consider elastic single-particle scattering from a one-dimensional
two-component trapped superfluid Fermi gas when the incoming projectile
particle is identical to one of the confined species. Our theoretical treatment
is based on the Hartree-Fock ground state of the trapped gas and a
configuration-interaction description of the excitations. We determine the
scattering phase shifts for the system and predict Fano-type scattering
resonances that are a direct consequence of inter-atomic pairing. We describe
the main characteristics of the scattering resonances and make a comparison
with the results of BCS mean-field theory.
</abstract></arXivRaw>
