<metadata>
 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.4305</id><submitter>Stuart Hastings</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Wed, 26 Nov 2008 13:37:44 GMT</date><size>13kb</size></version><title>An Elementary Approach to a Model Problem of Lagerstrom</title><authors>S. P. Hastings and J. B. McLeod</authors><categories>math.CA</categories><msc-class>34E05, 41A60</msc-class><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  The equation studied is u&quot;+((n-1)/r)u'+epsilon u u'+ku'^{2}=0, with boundary
conditions u(1)=0, u(infinity)=1. This model equation has been studied by many
authors since it was introduced in the 1950s by P. A. Lagerstrom. We use an
elementary approach to show that there is an infinite series solution which is
uniformly convergent on 1&lt;=r&lt;infinity. The first few terms are easily derived,
from which one quickly deduces the inner and outer asymptotic expansions, with
no matching procedure or a priori assumptions about the nature of the
expansion. We also give a short and elementary existence and uniqueness proof
which covers all epsilon &gt; 0, k &gt;= 0, and n &gt;= 1.
</abstract></arXivRaw>
