 <id>0811.4355</id><submitter>Krzysztof Pachucki</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Wed, 26 Nov 2008 16:08:09 GMT</date><size>25kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Sat, 24 Jan 2009 14:35:50 GMT</date><size>24kb</size></version><title>Nonadiabatic corrections to rovibrational levels of H$_2$</title><authors>Krzysztof Pachucki and Jacek Komasa</authors><categories>physics.chem-ph</categories><comments>14 pages</comments><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  The leading nonadiabatic corrections to rovibrational levels of a diatomic
molecule are expressed in terms of three functions of internuclear distance:
corrections to the adiabatic potential, the effective nuclear mass, and the
effective moment of inertia. The resulting radial Schr\&quot;odinger equation for
nuclear motion is solved numerically yielding accurate nonadiabatic energies
for all rovibrational levels of H$_2$ molecule in excellent agreement with
previous calculations by Wolniewicz.
