 <id>0811.4410</id><submitter>Enrico Calzavarini</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Wed, 26 Nov 2008 20:19:21 GMT</date><size>46kb</size></version><version version='v2'><date>Wed, 26 Nov 2008 23:13:52 GMT</date><size>46kb</size></version><title>Acceleration statistics of finite-sized particles in turbulent flow: the
  role of Faxen forces</title><authors>Enrico Calzavarini, Romain Volk, Mickael Bourgoin, Emmanuel Leveque,
  Jean-Francois Pinton and Federico Toschi</authors><categories>physics.flu-dyn</categories><comments>10 pages, 4 figures</comments><journal-ref>J. Fluid Mech. 630, pp. 179 - 189 (2009)</journal-ref><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  The dynamics of particles in turbulence when the particle-size is larger than
