 <arXivRaw xsi:schemaLocation='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/ http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw.xsd' xmlns='http://arxiv.org/OAI/arXivRaw/' xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'>
 <id>0811.4526</id><submitter>Rumyantsev Dmitry Alexandrovich</submitter><version version='v1'><date>Thu, 27 Nov 2008 12:38:54 GMT</date><size>256kb</size></version><title>Influence of the photon - neutrino processes on magnetar cooling</title><authors>M.V. Chistyakov, D.A. Rumyantsev</authors><categories>astro-ph</categories><comments>8 pages, LaTeX, 2 PS figures, based on the talk presented by D.A.
  Rumyantsev at the XV International Seminar Quarks'2008, Sergiev Posad, Moscow
  Region, May 23-29, 2008, to appear in the Proceedings</comments><license>http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/</license><abstract>  The photon-neutrino processes $\gamma e^{\pm} \to e^{\pm} \nu \bar \nu$,
$\gamma \to \nu \bar \nu$ and $\gamma \gamma \to \nu \bar \nu$ are investigated
in the presence of a strongly magnetized and dense electron-positron plasma.
The amplitudes of the reactions $\gamma e^{\pm} \to e^{\pm} \nu \bar \nu$ and
$\gamma \gamma \to \nu \bar \nu$ are obtained. In the case of a cold degenerate
plasma contributions of the considering processes to neutrino emissivity are
calculated. It is shown that contribution of the process $\gamma \gamma \to \nu
\bar \nu$ to neutrino emissivity is supressed in comparision with the
contributions of the processes $\gamma e^{\pm} \to e^{\pm} \nu \bar \nu$ and
$\gamma \to \nu \bar \nu$. The constraint on the magnetic field strength in the
magnetar outer crust is obtained.
